[19967, 3, 1090595, 1155810, "It was narrated that Abu Musa said:", "\"The Messenger of Allah [ﷺ] said: 'Every intoxicant is unlawful.'\"", null, null, "Sahih (Darussalam)", null, "Book 51, Hadith 57", null, "Vol. 6, Book 51, Hadith 5598", "en"]
[19968, 3, 1090600, 1155820, "It was narrated from Abu Burdah that his father said:", "\"The Messenger of Allah [ﷺ] sent Mu'adh and me to Yemen. Mu'adh said: 'You are sending us to a land where the people have many kinds of drinks. What should I drink?' He said: 'Drink, but do not drink any intoxicant.'\"", null, null, "Sahih (Darussalam)", null, "Book 51, Hadith 58", null, "Vol. 6, Book 51, Hadith 5599", "en"]
[19969, 3, 1090605, 1155830, "It was narrated that Abu Musa said:", "\"The Messenger of Allah [ﷺ] said: 'Every intoxicant is unlawful.'\"", null, null, "Sahih (Darussalam)", null, "Book 51, Hadith 59", null, "Vol. 6, Book 51, Hadith 5600", "en"]
[19970, 3, 1090610, 1155840, "Al-Aswad bin Shaiban As-Sadusi said:", "\"I heard 'Ata' being asked by a man: 'We travel and drinks are offered to us in the marketplaces, and we do not know what kind of vessels they were prepared in.' He said: 'Every intoxicant is unlawful.' He repeated the question and he said: 'Every intoxicant is unlawful.' He repeated the question and he said: 'It is as I have told you.'\"", null, null, "Sahih (Darussalam)", null, "Book 51, Hadith 60", null, "Vol. 6, Book 51, Hadith 5601", "en"]
[19971, 3, 1090615, 1155850, "It was narrated that Ibn Sirin said:", "\"Every intoxicant is unlawful.\"", null, null, "Sahih (Darussalam)", null, "Book 51, Hadith 61", null, "Vol. 6, Book 51, Hadith 5602", "en"]
[19972, 3, 1090620, 1155860, "It was narrated that 'Abdul-Malik bin At-Tufail Al-Jazari said:", "\"Umar bin 'Abdul-Aziz wrote to us, saying: 'Do not drink the thickened juice of grapes (obtained by boiling it down) until two-third of it has gone and one-third is left. And every intoxicant is unlawful.'\"", null, null, "Da'if (Darussalam)", null, "Book 51, Hadith 62", null, "Vol. 6, Book 51, Hadith 5603", "en"]
[19973, 3, 1090625, 1155870, "It was narrated that As-Sa'q bin Hazn said:", "\"Umar bin 'Abdul-'Aziz wrote to 'Adiy bin Artah (saying): 'Every intoxicant is unlawful.'\"", null, null, "Hasan (Darussalam)", null, "Book 51, Hadith 63", null, "Vol. 6, Book 51, Hadith 5604", "en"]
[19974, 3, 1090630, 1155880, "It was narrated from Abu Musa Al-Ash'ari that:", "The Messenger of Allah [ﷺ] said: \"Every intoxicant is unlawful.\"", null, null, "Sahih (Darussalam)", null, "Book 51, Hadith 64", null, "Vol. 6, Book 51, Hadith 5605", "en"]
[19975, 3, 1090635, 1155890, "Abu Bakr bin Abi Musa narrated that his father said:", "\"The Messenger of Allah [ﷺ] sent me to Yemen and I said: 'O Messenger of Allah, there are (different kinds of) drinks there, what should I drink, and what should I refrain from?' He said: 'What are they?' I said: 'Al-Bit' (mead) and Al-Mizr (beer).' He said: 'What are mead and beer?' I said: 'Mead is a drink made from honey and beer is a drink made from grains.' The Messenger of Allah [ﷺ] said: 'Do not drink any intoxicant, for I have forbidden all intoxicants.'\"", null, null, "Hasan (Darussalam)", null, "Book 51, Hadith 65", null, "Vol. 6, Book 51, Hadith 5606", "en"]
[19976, 3, 1090640, 1155900, "It was narrated from Abu Burdah that his father said:", "\"The Messenger of Allah [ﷺ] sent me to Yemen and I said: 'O Messenger of Allah, there are drinks there which they call Al-Bit' (mead) and Al-Mizr (beer).' He said: 'What is mead (and beer)?' I said: 'A drink made from honey, and beer is made from barley.' He said: 'Every intoxicant is unlawful.'\"", null, null, "Sahih (Darussalam)", null, "Book 51, Hadith 66", null, "Vol. 6, Book 51, Hadith 5607", "en"]
[19977, 3, 1090645, 1155910, "It was narrated that Ibn 'Umar said:", "\"The Messenger of Allah [ﷺ] delivered a Khutbah and quoted the Verse about Khamr. A man said: 'O Messenger of Allah, what do you think about Al-Mizr (beer)?' He said: 'What is beer?' He said: 'A (drink) from grains that is made in Yemen.' He said: 'Does it intoxicate?' He said: 'Yes.' He said: 'Every intoxicant is unlawful.'\"", null, null, "Sahih (Darussalam)", null, "Book 51, Hadith 67", null, "Vol. 6, Book 51, Hadith 5608", "en"]
[19978, 3, 1090650, 1155920, "It was narrated that Abu Al-Juwairiyah said:", "\"I heard Ibn 'Abbas when he was asked: 'Advise us about Badhiq (a drink made from the juice of grapes slightly boiled).' He said: 'Muhammad came before Badhiq (i.e., it was not known during his time), but everything that intoxicates is unlawful.'\"", null, null, "Sahih (Darussalam)", null, "Book 51, Hadith 68", null, "Vol. 6, Book 51, Hadith 5609", "en"]
[19979, 3, 1090655, 1155930, "'Amr bin Shu'aib narrated from his father, from his grandfather, that:", "The Prophet (ﷺ) [ﷺ] said: \"What intoxicates in large amounts, a small amount of it is unlawful.\"", null, null, "Hasan (Darussalam)", null, "Book 51, Hadith 69", null, "Vol. 6, Book 51, Hadith 5610", "en"]
[19980, 3, 1090660, 1155940, "It was narrated from 'Amir bin Sa'd, from his father, that:", "The Prophet (ﷺ) [ﷺ] said: \"I forbid to you small amounts of whatever intoxicates in large amounts.\"", null, null, "Hasan (Darussalam)", null, "Book 51, Hadith 70", null, "Vol. 6, Book 51, Hadith 5611", "en"]
[19981, 3, 1090665, 1155950, "It was narrated from 'Amir bin Sa'd, from his father, that:", "The Prophet (ﷺ) [ﷺ] forbade a small amount of whatever intoxicates in large amounts.", null, null, "Hasan (Darussalam)", null, "Book 51, Hadith 71", null, "Vol. 6, Book 51, Hadith 5612", "en"]
[19982, 3, 1090670, 1155960, "It was narrated that Abu Hurairah said:", "\"I know that the Messenger of Allah [ﷺ] was fasting, so I prepared some Nabidh for him to break his fast that I had prepared for him in a gourd. I brought it to him and he said: 'Bring it here.' So I brought it closer and it was bubbling. He said: 'Throw it against the wall (throw it away), for this is the drink of one who does not believe in Allah or the Last Day.'\"", null, null, "Sahih (Darussalam)", null, "Book 51, Hadith 72", null, "Vol. 6, Book 51, Hadith 5613", "en"]
[19983, 3, 1090675, 1155970, "It was narrated that 'Ali - may Allah honor his face - said:", "\"The Prophet (ﷺ) [ﷺ] forbade to me to use gold rings, Al-Qassi, Al-Mitharah and Al-Ji'ah (a barley drink).\"", null, null, "Sahih (Darussalam)", null, "Book 51, Hadith 73", null, "Vol. 6, Book 51, Hadith 5614", "en"]
[19984, 3, 1090680, 1155980, "Sa'sa'ah said to 'Ali bin Abi Talib - may Allah honor his face - :", "\"Forbid to us, O Commander of the Believers! What the Messenger of Allah [ﷺ] forbade to you.\" He said: \"The Messenger of Allah [ﷺ] forbade me from using Ad-Dubba' and Al-Hantam.\"", null, null, "Sahih (Darussalam)", null, "Book 51, Hadith 74", null, "Vol. 6, Book 51, Hadith 5615", "en"]
[19985, 3, 1090685, 1155990, "It was narrated from Jabir that :", "(fruits) would be soaked for the Prophet (ﷺ) [ﷺ] in a small vessel made of stone.", null, null, "Sahih (Darussalam)", null, "Book 51, Hadith 75", null, "Vol. 6, Book 51, Hadith 5616", "en"]
[19986, 3, 1090690, 1156000, "It was narrated that Tawus said:", "\"A man said to Ibn 'Umar: 'Did the Messenger of Allah [ﷺ] forbid soaking (fruits) in earthenware jars?' He said: 'Yes.' Tawus said: 'By Allah, I heard that from him.'\"", null, null, "Sahih (Darussalam)", null, "Book 51, Hadith 76", null, "Vol. 6, Book 51, Hadith 5617", "en"]
[19987, 3, 1090695, 1156010, "It was narrated that Sulaiman At-Taimi and Ibrahim bin Maisarah said:", "\"We heard Tawus say: 'A man came to Ibn 'Umar and said: Did the Messenger of Allah [ﷺ] forbid soaking (fruits) in earthenware jars? He said: 'Yes.' Ibrahim added in his Hadith: \"And Ad-Dubba' (gourds).'\"", null, null, "Sahih (Darussalam)", null, "Book 51, Hadith 77", null, "Vol. 6, Book 51, Hadith 5618", "en"]
[19988, 3, 1090700, 1156020, "Ibn 'Abbas said:", "\"The Messenger of Allah [ﷺ] forbade soaking (fruits) in earthenware jars.\"", null, null, "Sahih (Darussalam)", null, "Book 51, Hadith 78", null, "Vol. 6, Book 51, Hadith 5619", "en"]
[19989, 3, 1090705, 1156030, "It was narrated that Ibn 'Umar said:", "\"The Messenger of Allah [ﷺ] forbade Al-Hantam. I (the narrator) said: \"What is Al-Hantam?\" He said: \"The earthenware jar.\"", null, null, "Sahih (Darussalam)", null, "Book 51, Hadith 79", null, "Vol. 6, Book 51, Hadith 5620", "en"]
[19990, 3, 1090710, 1156040, "It was narrated that Abu Maslamah said:", "\"I heard 'Abdul-'Aziz - that is, bin Asid At-Tahi from Al-Basrah - say: 'Ibn Az-Zubair was asked about soaking (fruits) in earthenware jars and he said: \"The Messenger of Allah [ﷺ] forbade us from that.\"", null, null, "Hasan (Darussalam)", null, "Book 51, Hadith 80", null, "Vol. 6, Book 51, Hadith 5621", "en"]
[19991, 3, 1090715, 1156050, "It was narrated that Sa'eed bin Jubair said:", "\"We asked Ibn 'Umar about Nabidh made in an earthenware jar and he said: 'The Messenger of Allah [ﷺ] forbade that.' So I went to Ibn 'Abbas and said to him: 'Today I heard something that surprised me.' He said: 'What was it?' I said: 'I asked Ibn 'Umar about Nabidh made in an earthenware jar and he said: The Messenger of Allah [ﷺ] forbade it.' He said: 'Ibn 'Umar spoke the truth.' I said: 'What is an earthenware jar?' He said: 'Anything that is made of clay.'\"", null, null, "Sahih (Darussalam)", null, "Book 51, Hadith 81", null, "Vol. 6, Book 51, Hadith 5622", "en"]
[19992, 3, 1090720, 1156060, "It was narrated that Sa'eed bin Jubair said:", "\"I was with Ibn 'Umar when he was asked about Nabidh made in an earthenware jar. He said: 'The Messenger of Allah [ﷺ] forbade it.' I got upset when I heard that, so I went to Ibn 'Abbas and said: 'Ibn 'Umar was asked about something, and I found it difficult.' He said: 'What was it?' I said: 'He was asked about Nabidh made in an earthenware jar.' He said: 'He spoke the truth; the Messenger of Allah [ﷺ] forbade it.' I said: 'What is an earthenware jar?' He said: 'Anything that is made of clay.'\"", null, null, "Sahih (Darussalam)", null, "Book 51, Hadith 82", null, "Vol. 6, Book 51, Hadith 5623", "en"]
[19992, 3, 1090720, 1156060, "It was narrated that Sa'eed bin Jubair said:", "\"I was with Ibn 'Umar when he was asked about Nabidh made in an earthenware jar. He said: 'The Messenger of Allah [ﷺ] forbade it.' I got upset when I heard that, so I went to Ibn 'Abbas and said: 'Ibn 'Umar was asked about something, and I found it difficult.' He said: 'What was it?' I said: 'He was asked about Nabidh made in an earthenware jar.' He said: 'He spoke the truth; the Messenger of Allah [ﷺ] forbade it.' I said: 'What is an earthenware jar?' He said: 'Anything that is made of clay.'\"", null, null, "Sahih (Darussalam)", null, "Book 51, Hadith 82", null, "Vol. 6, Book 51, Hadith 5623", "en"]
[19993, 3, 1090725, 1156070, "It was narrated that Ash-Shaibani said:", "\"I heard Ibn Abi Awfa say: 'The Messenger of Allah [ﷺ] forbade Nabidh made in green earthenware jars.' I said: 'And white ones?' He said: 'I do not know.'\"", null, null, "Sahih (Darussalam)", null, "Book 51, Hadith 83", null, "Vol. 6, Book 51, Hadith 5624", "en"]
[19994, 3, 1090730, 1156080, "Abu Ishaq Ash-Shaibani said:", "\"I heard Ibn Abi Awfa say: 'The Messenger of Allah [ﷺ] forbade Nabidh made in green and white earthenware jars.'\"", null, null, "Sahih (Darussalam)", null, "Book 51, Hadith 84", null, "Vol. 6, Book 51, Hadith 5625", "en"]
[19995, 3, 1090735, 1156090, "It was narrated that Abu Raja' said:", "\"I asked Al-Hasan about Nabidh made in earthenware jars - is it unlawful? He said: '(It is) unlawful. One who would not lie narrated to us that the Messenger of Allah [ﷺ] forbade Nabidh made in Al-Hantam, Ad-Dubba' (gourds), Al-Muzaffat and An-Naqir.'\"", null, null, "Sahih (Darussalam)", null, "Book 51, Hadith 85", null, "Vol. 6, Book 51, Hadith 5626", "en"]
